{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/plugins","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Plugins!</p>\n<p>Yes vim does get better.</p>\n<p>Yes, that not so pretty language VimL is a primary vehicle in making things\nnice.  In NeoVim you can use Lua, which is quite nice.  Especially when you\nconsider that there is a Typescript -> lua converter.  Which means you can use\na typed language and get type completion and create vim plugins.  42069IQ</p>\n<h3 id=\"get-a-plugin-manager\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#get-a-plugin-manager\" aria-label=\"get a plugin manager permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Get a Plugin Manager</h3>\n<p>Plug!</p>\n<p>Lets follow the instructions together getting\n<a href=\"https://github.com/junegunn/vim-plug\">Plug</a> vim plugin manager installed</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">... plays waiting music ...</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"file-navigation-20\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#file-navigation-20\" aria-label=\"file navigation 20 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>File Navigation 2.0</h3>\n<p>Let's add a fuzzy finder, remap some things, and make it work for us.  We are\ngoing to use FZF even though I Use telescope personally.  The reason for this\nis because Telescope is neovim specific (lua) and wont work with Vim.  Where as\nFZF has been working for some time with vim.</p>\n<p>Lets add the following lines to your vimrc</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">call plug#begin(&#39;~/.vim/plugged&#39;)\n\nPlug &#39;junegunn/fzf&#39;, { &#39;do&#39;: { -&gt; fzf#install() } }\nPlug &#39;junegunn/fzf.vim&#39;\n\ncall plug#end()</code></pre></div>\n<p>Our vimrc should look something like the following.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">set scrolloff=8\nset number\nset relativenumber\nset tabstop=4 softtabstop=4\nset shiftwidth=4\nset expandtab\nset smartindent\n\ncall plug#begin(&#39;~/.vim/plugged&#39;)\n\nPlug &#39;junegunn/fzf&#39;, { &#39;do&#39;: { -&gt; fzf#install() } }\nPlug &#39;junegunn/fzf.vim&#39;\n\ncall plug#end()\n\n&quot; This was from the colorscheme section\ncolorscheme desert\n\n&quot; Our remaps\nlet mapleader = &quot; &quot;\nnnoremap &lt;leader&gt;pv :Vex&lt;CR&gt;\nnnoremap &lt;Leader&gt;&lt;CR&gt; :so ~/.config/nvim/init.vim&lt;CR&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Lets source our vimrc</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">&quot; or use your sweet remap\n:so %</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now we need to execute our plugin manager.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">:PlugInstall</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"warning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#warning\" aria-label=\"warning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>WARNING</h3>\n<h3 id=\"my-vim-colorscheme-is-just-a-default-one-its-ugly\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-vim-colorscheme-is-just-a-default-one-its-ugly\" aria-label=\"my vim colorscheme is just a default one its ugly permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My Vim Colorscheme is just a default one, its ugly</h3>\n<p>Once you do this you should see the following menu</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/9efb3/plug-install.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Plug Result\"\n        title=\"Plug Result\"\n        src=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/5a190/plug-install.png\"\n        srcset=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/772e8/plug-install.png 200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/e17e5/plug-install.png 400w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/5a190/plug-install.png 800w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/c1b63/plug-install.png 1200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/29007/plug-install.png 1600w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0d8bbf4f8d28d6010a798a1210459a8a/9efb3/plug-install.png 1894w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Now we can execute <code class=\"language-text\">:GFiles</code>, lets give it a try in <code class=\"language-text\">vim-nav-playground</code>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/81ebd/fzf-results.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"FZF Result\"\n        title=\"FZF Result\"\n        src=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/5a190/fzf-results.png\"\n        srcset=\"/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/772e8/fzf-results.png 200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/e17e5/fzf-results.png 400w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/5a190/fzf-results.png 800w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/c1b63/fzf-results.png 1200w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/29007/fzf-results.png 1600w,\n/vim-fundamentals/static/0ebc3a3b4b96b1fef45503305d710cbc/81ebd/fzf-results.png 1868w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"what-have-i-taught-you\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-have-i-taught-you\" aria-label=\"what have i taught you permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>WHAT HAVE I TAUGHT YOU?</h3>\n<p>What should we do now?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>M A K E _ A _ R E M A P</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">nnoremap &lt;C-p&gt; :GFiles&lt;CR&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"recap\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#recap\" aria-label=\"recap permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Recap</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>We got a plugin manager that makes installing plugins easy!  You just need\nthe path on github to install new ones.</li>\n<li>We installed FZF, made a remap! then showed how awesome it is.</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/plugins","title":"Plugins","order":"30A","section":"Plugins","description":"Lets beef up the RC!"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"53A","path":"/pit-stop","title":"Pit Stop"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"51A","path":"/macros","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"54A","path":"/adv-motions","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"50A","path":"/search-and-replace","title":"Search And Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"52A","path":"/registers","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/are-you-ready","title":"Are You Ready?"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"5A","path":"/basic-usage","title":"Using Vim"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"70A","path":"/exercise-1","title":"dyp"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"71A","path":"/exercise-2","title":"insert"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"69A","path":"/exercise-0","title":"hjkl-x"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"72A","path":"/exercise-3","title":"Search and Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"10A","path":"/color-my-pencils","title":"Color My Pencils"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"73A","path":"/exercise-4","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"74A","path":"/exercise-5","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"15A","path":"/files-marks","title":